original: Linden, Hans, länsarkitekt, Växjö, f. 26/9’/08 i Örebro av prosten Theo-dor L. o. Ruth Melander. G. 38 m. Kerstin Ekrelius. Barn: Agneta f. 39, Per 41, Ellika 43, Karin 47. — Stud:ex. i Örebro 28, utex. fr. KTH 33, stud:re-sor i Tvskl., Tjeckoslov. o. Österr. 28, Ital. m. fl. 33, 37, 38 o. 47, Egypten, Palest. o. Syr. 30. Priv. konditioner 33’-36, anst. inom länsarkit :org. som assist, i Malmö 36-40, som bitr. länsarkit. i Karlskrona 40-41 samt som länsarkit. i Växjö sed. 41. Kronoombud i lokala värder:ndn sed. 42, sekr. i Kronob. läns hemslöjdsfören. 43-45. Hobbies : målning, botanik. RNO.
translated: Linden, Hans, County Architect, Växjö, born on September 26, 1908 in Örebro, to Reverend Theodore L. and Ruth Melander. Married in 1938 to Kerstin Ekrelius. Children: Agneta born in 1939, Per in 1941, Ellika in 1943, and Karin in 1947. Completed high school in Örebro in 1928, graduated from KTH (Royal Institute of Technology) in 1933, studied in Germany, Czechoslovakia, and Austria in 1928, Italy and others in 1933, 1937, 1938, and 1947, and visited Egypt, Palestine, and Syria in 1930. Private engagements from 1933 to 1936, worked within the county architect organization as an assistant in Malmö from 1936 to 1940, as an assistant county architect in Karlskrona from 1940 to 1941, and as a county architect in Växjö since 1941. Appointed as a representative in the local valuation committee since 1942, and secretary in the county handicraft association from 1943 to 1945. Hobbies include painting and botany. Honorary member of the Royal Order of the Northern Star.
